This paper is primarily focused on improving the detection accuracy of Android malicious apps, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to analyze the collected data, which can be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses the security issues in Android-based smart devices, which can be classified under software engineering (cs.SE). The use of machine learning algorithms to analyze the collected data can also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves the use of data grouping techniques to improve the detection accuracy, which can be classified under data science (cs.DS).
